article.headline: Temple 60, Penn State 47
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- David Hawkins scored 25 points and Mardy Collins added 15 to lead Temple to a 67-56 win over Penn State Saturday. Despite shooting 20 percent from the field in the second half and going 11:01 without a field goal, the Owls (2-4) beat the Nittany Lions by forcing 19 turnovers and hitting 14 of 17 free-throw attempts down the stretch. DeForrest Riley-Smith led Penn State (3-4) with 17 points, including five 3-pointers. Marlon Smith scored 12. Hawkins had 19 points in the first half, including seven during a 19-2 run that snapped a 26-26 tie and put Temple up 17 at halftime. Smith -- who was held scoreless in Wednesday's 60-47 loss to Rutgers -- hit three 3s in the first half. The Nittany Lions had a season-high 11 on the day, but missed 12 in a row at one point. Freshman Mario Taybron had a season-high eight assists for Temple. Penn State's Ben Luber had 11. The Owls have won four straight against the Nittany Lions, a streak that began with a Sweet 16 win in 2001.
